The paper deals with stability analysis of Kalman filtering over a specific type of channel, namely Gilbert-Elliott channels. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of linear matrix inequalities (LMIs) and stochastic processes, which are common in the fields of numerical analysis (cs.NI) and applied mathematics (cs.MA). Finally, the paper presents theoretical results and proofs, which are often found in the machine learning (cs.LG) literature.
